ws the ring next to the L-shape, but they are on opposite faces of the net; one option the triangle is rotated the wrong way; one option shows a cross, which is not on the net at all. The remaining cube is consistent with the net.', false),
  (109, 2, 'Each figure is labelled with its code. Work out what each letter stands for, then select the code for the final figure.
